WEBVTT

00:19.022 --> 00:20.435
<i>Previously on</i> Tyrant...

00:20.460 --> 00:21.941
COGSWELL: <i>There's been some chatter</i>

00:21.966 --> 00:24.199
<i>about something bigger
planned, but we don't know where,</i>

00:24.224 --> 00:25.923
<i>and we don't know when.</i>

00:25.948 --> 00:27.868
I'll kill them all if I have to.

00:27.903 --> 00:30.537
<i>I have authorized our
security forces to arrest</i>

00:30.573 --> 00:31.872
<i>anyone who has collaborated</i>

00:31.907 --> 00:34.174
- <i>with terrorists.</i>
- I need to see Ihab.

00:34.209 --> 00:35.409
Face-to-face.

00:35.444 --> 00:37.544
You're finally waking up to the truth.

00:37.580 --> 00:40.146
I'm asking you to give me a
chance to win this election.

00:40.182 --> 00:41.548
There will be no election.

00:41.584 --> 00:43.984
<i>Oh, but there will be a war.</i>

00:44.019 --> 00:45.696
MALOOF: <i>And when Al-Qadi
comes home, we'll be waiting.</i>

00:45.720 --> 00:47.687
BARRY: <i>We'll find him and
we'll kill him, too.</i>

00:47.722 --> 00:49.722
- Welcome home.
- BARRY: <i>Your brother-in-law</i>

00:49.758 --> 00:50.790
was in contact

00:50.825 --> 00:53.026
with Ihab to arrange the
meeting the very same day

00:53.061 --> 00:55.996
<i>that he plotted the
massacre at the Commission.</i>

00:56.031 --> 00:57.797
Go ahead, arrest me.

00:57.832 --> 00:59.933
You're gonna be put on trial
for who you really are.

00:59.968 --> 01:01.846
REPORTER: The government of
President Bassam Al Fayeed

01:01.870 --> 01:03.236
has formally banned

01:03.272 --> 01:04.672
<i>Sheik Hussein Al-Qadi from standing</i>

01:04.706 --> 01:06.273
<i>in the presidential election.</i>

01:06.308 --> 01:08.008
This violence is taking its toll

01:08.043 --> 01:09.542
on Bassam's support.

01:09.577 --> 01:14.381
I'm resigning my
post as Foreign Secretary.

01:14.792 --> 01:16.325
MALOOF: Professor Haitham El-Amin.

01:16.360 --> 01:19.628
He's part of a new generation
of anti-government bloggers.

01:19.664 --> 01:21.138
This guy's the most influential.

01:21.276 --> 01:22.942
You're sleeping with Professor El-Amin.

01:22.966 --> 01:25.066
He's been writing blogs about
me being responsible

01:25.102 --> 01:26.735
<i>for the violence in Abuddin.</i>

01:26.771 --> 01:28.067
I'm in love for the first time

01:28.197 --> 01:29.570
<i>in 25 years.</i>

01:29.606 --> 01:30.505
Just so you know,

01:30.540 --> 01:33.541
I'm not gonna go easy
on the administration.

01:33.576 --> 01:35.443
You might come under fire yourself.

01:35.478 --> 01:37.012
Anything else?

01:37.047 --> 01:38.599
Yes.

01:39.307 --> 01:41.521
I'm going to win this election.

01:43.411 --> 01:45.611
(crickets chirping)

01:48.049 --> 01:50.783
(breathing deeply)

01:53.955 --> 01:55.387
(groans)

01:55.423 --> 01:56.923
Daliyah?

02:05.667 --> 02:08.434
Don't worry, it won't stain.

02:11.939 --> 02:14.639
Remember when I got this shirt?

02:14.675 --> 02:18.477
We went to that giant
mall in Orange County.

02:18.512 --> 02:22.013
Mom got you that hoodie you
thought looked feminine.

02:22.048 --> 02:24.215
Right, it was pink.

02:24.250 --> 02:26.184
It was lavender.

02:27.921 --> 02:30.522
Emma, honey, you woke me up again.

02:30.557 --> 02:32.891
I'm sorry.

02:32.926 --> 02:35.460
Do you want me to sing you a lullaby?

02:36.763 --> 02:40.131
No, sweetheart, I just
need you to let me sleep.

02:40.166 --> 02:41.332
Well,

02:41.368 --> 02:44.703
is he dead yet?

02:48.375 --> 02:50.942
Not yet.

02:53.146 --> 02:55.480
Soon.

02:55.515 --> 02:57.448
That's what you said last time.

03:00.253 --> 03:02.520
(inhales deeply)

03:02.555 --> 03:05.323
I'm trying, sweetie.

03:05.358 --> 03:08.026
Try harder.

03:09.862 --> 03:12.163
(sobbing)

03:14.700 --> 03:17.835
(whispering): Bassam?

03:17.870 --> 03:20.938
Bassam.

03:22.442 --> 03:24.975
You're shaking.

03:25.011 --> 03:27.378
(sighs)

03:27.414 --> 03:29.613
(breathing heavily)

03:34.921 --> 03:37.287
I'm so sorry I'm late, but honestly,

03:37.322 --> 03:39.790
you don't have to wait up for me.

03:46.065 --> 03:50.233
I'm going to meet with Al-Qadi tomorrow.

03:53.839 --> 03:55.005
What?

03:55.041 --> 03:56.774
I know I might be
playing with fire, but...

03:56.809 --> 03:59.009
In more ways than you think.

04:01.047 --> 04:03.681
These were sent to the campaign today.

04:10.656 --> 04:12.155
Who sent them?

04:12.191 --> 04:14.658
Someone who's trying to
embarrass you, obviously.

04:14.694 --> 04:17.127
Why send them here? Why
not post them online?

04:17.161 --> 04:18.495
Money.

04:18.529 --> 04:20.762
He wants 50,000 U.S. dollars.

04:20.798 --> 04:24.468
Which I will pay him in
order to shut this down.

04:24.503 --> 04:27.870
But this has to stop.

04:28.840 --> 04:31.308
Safiya said she'll take care of it.

04:31.343 --> 04:34.544
Maybe I better do that.

04:34.580 --> 04:35.745
I don't think that's smart.

04:35.780 --> 04:37.880
I think we should keep our distance.

04:37.916 --> 04:40.650
My sister is very resourceful.

04:40.685 --> 04:42.652
It will be safer that way.

04:44.389 --> 04:46.523
Are we being stupid?

04:49.528 --> 04:52.762
We have a lot to lose, both of us.

04:54.466 --> 04:56.633
Take off your clothes.

05:18.456 --> 05:20.689
(both breathing heavily)

05:27.965 --> 05:30.232
I want two things in my life.

05:35.439 --> 05:38.274
I want to do my job...

05:38.309 --> 05:39.808
and I want you.

05:44.882 --> 05:47.282
I'm not afraid of taking risks.

05:49.086 --> 05:52.754
Not being alive.

05:52.790 --> 05:55.057
That's what I'm afraid of.

06:25.089 --> 06:27.122
♪ ♪

06:29.658 --> 06:31.892
(both grunt)

06:56.252 --> 06:57.551
(breathing shakily)

06:57.586 --> 06:58.986
Are you all right?

06:59.021 --> 07:00.221
(exhales)

07:01.758 --> 07:03.357
(clears throat)

07:03.392 --> 07:04.859
I can go.

07:08.597 --> 07:11.330
No, no.

07:11.366 --> 07:13.099
Stay.

07:20.142 --> 07:21.775
(both moaning)

07:33.454 --> 07:36.422
(Ihab moaning louder)

07:50.772 --> 07:53.306
FAUZI: If Sheik Al-Qadi
is guilty of a crime,

07:53.341 --> 07:54.674
let him be charged with it.

07:54.709 --> 07:57.142
But whether he's worthy of office

07:57.178 --> 07:59.912
is for the people of Abuddin to decide

07:59.947 --> 08:01.480
and not the sitting president.

08:01.516 --> 08:03.683
Now, I may be the heir

08:03.718 --> 08:06.485
to my friend, Bassam's, revolution,

08:06.521 --> 08:08.521
but I'm not his twin.

08:08.556 --> 08:10.356
And on this we disagree.

08:10.391 --> 08:13.225
And my administration will reflect that.

08:13.260 --> 08:15.328
Truth.

08:15.363 --> 08:16.495
Reconciliation.

08:16.531 --> 08:19.799
Those powerful words ring hollow now.

08:19.834 --> 08:21.166
(TV turns off) He's winning.

08:21.202 --> 08:23.436
He doesn't need to say these things.

08:24.639 --> 08:26.305
What?

08:26.341 --> 08:29.208
He is allowed to disagree with you.

08:29.243 --> 08:30.508
Even in public.

08:30.544 --> 08:31.977
You think he's right, don't you?

08:32.011 --> 08:33.544
I didn't say that.

08:33.580 --> 08:35.080
No, you didn't say it, but you do.

08:36.717 --> 08:38.082
I think he's right.

08:38.118 --> 08:40.784
Did you two talk about this?

08:40.821 --> 08:42.754
What?

08:42.789 --> 08:45.324
No, you sound paranoid.

08:45.359 --> 08:47.726
You know, I wish people would
stop saying that to me.

08:47.761 --> 08:48.961
He loves you.

08:48.996 --> 08:52.630
We both do. We're both concerned.

08:52.666 --> 08:53.798
Separately.

08:53.834 --> 08:55.067
Are you?

08:56.603 --> 08:57.769
Yes.

08:57.804 --> 08:59.938
Neither one of you has any idea

08:59.974 --> 09:02.407
- what it is like to do this job.
- You're right.

09:02.442 --> 09:04.843
To be the one charged with
keeping people safe.

09:04.879 --> 09:06.912
- When there's no room for mistakes.
- Of course.

09:06.947 --> 09:09.248
Fauzi doesn't have a
clue, and neither do you.

09:12.352 --> 09:14.452
I'm going to go.

09:14.488 --> 09:15.820
I should go.

09:15.856 --> 09:18.022
Wait, wait, wait.

09:18.958 --> 09:20.625
I'm sorry.

09:20.660 --> 09:22.193
Don't go.

09:23.463 --> 09:25.397
I don't want to waste our time together.

09:25.432 --> 09:27.365
It's the one thing I look forward to.

09:27.401 --> 09:31.369
I look forward to it,
too, more than you even know.

09:31.404 --> 09:33.938
But I'm not just the
woman you sleep with

09:33.973 --> 09:36.407
in some anonymous room.

09:36.442 --> 09:38.575
Take some time.

09:38.611 --> 09:40.011
Think.

09:40.046 --> 09:41.913
And try and sleep.

09:51.024 --> 09:52.656
This is dangerous.

09:52.691 --> 09:54.558
For both of us.

09:54.593 --> 09:55.826
Yes, it is.

09:55.861 --> 09:58.062
I'll start by saying thank you.

09:58.097 --> 10:00.298
I appreciate your resignation.

10:00.333 --> 10:01.865
Now, why am I here?

10:01.901 --> 10:03.301
I want to know what really happened

10:03.336 --> 10:05.069
when you met with Ihab bin Rashid.

10:05.104 --> 10:07.704
It won't matter. You won't believe me.

10:07.740 --> 10:10.073
Try me. (sighs)

10:11.676 --> 10:13.176
I thought I could convince him

10:13.211 --> 10:16.479
that we both want the
same thing for Abuddin.

10:16.514 --> 10:19.215
I was wrong.

10:19.251 --> 10:22.052
I assumed I could succeed or die.

10:22.087 --> 10:25.155
And I was prepared for both.

10:25.190 --> 10:27.557
I was wrong about that, too.

10:27.592 --> 10:28.825
I ended up being used.

10:28.860 --> 10:31.561
The Caliphate has two
enemies inside Abuddin

10:31.596 --> 10:32.795
that scare them:

10:32.831 --> 10:34.564
Bassam...

10:34.599 --> 10:37.533
and me.

10:37.569 --> 10:40.837
One photograph took care of both of us.

10:40.872 --> 10:42.872
I'm outlawed,

10:42.907 --> 10:45.608
and Bassam proved
himself the enemy of Islam.

10:46.845 --> 10:48.811
You think I'm lying?

10:48.847 --> 10:51.080
I think you're telling the truth.

10:51.115 --> 10:54.683
The offer you made Ihab,

10:54.718 --> 10:57.019
I'm offering you the same thing.

10:57.054 --> 10:59.654
- A partnership, between us.
- You?

10:59.690 --> 11:02.224
I will be the president and you
will be my prime minister.

11:02.259 --> 11:04.393
- Impossible.
- Nothing is impossible.

11:04.428 --> 11:07.129
Bassam said you could not
run, and you won't be running,

11:07.285 --> 11:08.017
I will.

11:08.162 --> 11:09.831
N-not that.

11:09.867 --> 11:11.500
We want different things, madam.

11:11.535 --> 11:14.569
No, we want the same thing...
To win this election.

11:14.605 --> 11:17.339
And, unfortunately, the
only way that will happen

11:17.375 --> 11:21.410
is for us to reach some
kind of compromise.

11:21.445 --> 11:23.612
Otherwise, Fauzi
Nidal is about to become

11:23.647 --> 11:25.079
the President of Abuddin.

11:26.416 --> 11:31.052
Some gulfs are too
wide to cross, I'm afraid.

11:48.539 --> 11:51.205
Better?

11:53.043 --> 11:56.945
We need to start somewhere.

11:56.980 --> 11:59.146
MOHAMMED: Our intelligence suggests

11:59.181 --> 12:00.893
that with the help of
the American military,

12:00.917 --> 12:02.950
their strength is growing rapidly.

12:02.985 --> 12:05.085
They are moving
towards a ground war with us.

12:05.120 --> 12:08.488
This is precisely the kind of mistake

12:08.524 --> 12:10.402
- we want Bassam to make.
- Not if it comes too soon.

12:10.426 --> 12:12.927
I worry that we won't
be ready for an onslaught

12:12.962 --> 12:14.628
from an American-backed Abuddinian Army.

12:14.664 --> 12:16.575
TALAL: Between the bombing
by the Russians and the Kurds

12:16.599 --> 12:19.332
on the ground, we've lost
more than 1,000 soldiers.

12:19.368 --> 12:20.901
IHAB: I wouldn't worry.

12:20.937 --> 12:23.704
When the holy war begins,

12:23.739 --> 12:25.305
the true believers will flock.

12:25.340 --> 12:28.075
The Americans will
arrive well before they do.

12:28.110 --> 12:29.443
You need to have more faith.

12:29.478 --> 12:31.645
- And you need to watch your place.
- My place?

12:31.681 --> 12:33.279
What place is that?

12:33.314 --> 12:34.213
Enough.

12:34.248 --> 12:36.849
Fighting among ourselves, losing focus.

12:36.885 --> 12:39.452
This doesn't help our cause.

12:39.487 --> 12:42.073
He's willing to kill us all to
avenge the death of a woman.

12:42.164 --> 12:43.000
TALAL: For Samira Nidal,

12:43.024 --> 12:44.490
we turn back to Abuddin?

12:45.860 --> 12:48.561
I want us back in Abuddin.

12:51.165 --> 12:52.710
COGSWELL: <i>The Bradley
Fighting Vehicles arrived</i>

12:52.734 --> 12:54.333
<i>from Europe this morning.</i>

12:54.368 --> 12:56.168
MALOOF: <i>You've added
3,700 ground soldiers</i>

12:56.204 --> 12:57.403
<i>in the past month.</i>

12:57.438 --> 12:58.972
BARRY: <i>You just need to tell me</i>

12:59.007 --> 13:00.172
if we're ready or not.

13:00.208 --> 13:01.641
We're ready, Mr. President.

13:01.676 --> 13:04.076
Very soon.

13:05.079 --> 13:06.479
You don't agree, General?

13:06.514 --> 13:08.981
MALOOF: General Cogswell
does not take into account

13:09.016 --> 13:11.049
the fervor of the Abuddinian soldiers,

13:11.085 --> 13:13.119
their willingness to
die for their country.

13:13.154 --> 13:16.822
I'm a little old for
macho optimism, Mr. President.

13:16.857 --> 13:18.491
Here's the truth.

13:18.526 --> 13:20.559
This is going to be a long war.

13:20.595 --> 13:23.629
Every war is longer than you
think it's going to be.

13:23.664 --> 13:25.231
You'll be strongest on your first day,

13:25.266 --> 13:27.233
and every day after
that, you'll get weaker

13:27.268 --> 13:28.400
and they'll get stronger.

13:28.436 --> 13:30.302
You're going to be mired in Syria,

13:30.338 --> 13:31.837
which is their territory.

13:31.872 --> 13:33.772
You think you know fervor, General?

13:33.807 --> 13:35.006
This is an end-of-days cult.

13:35.041 --> 13:37.642
You have no idea what real fervor is.

13:37.677 --> 13:40.311
Unless you overwhelm
them from the start,

13:40.347 --> 13:41.924
you're gonna fight
them to a draw at best,

13:41.948 --> 13:43.181
which means they win.

13:43.216 --> 13:45.250
And you've got one
chance to get it right.

13:45.285 --> 13:47.585
So until then, he does nothing?

13:47.722 --> 13:48.710
Correct.

13:48.735 --> 13:50.035
You're not ready to send in

13:50.060 --> 13:51.644
troops and you can't find
me Ihab and the sheik.

13:51.669 --> 13:53.925
- Mr. President...
- You two figure this out!

13:53.961 --> 13:55.961
This election is two months away.

13:55.996 --> 13:57.895
I'm running out of time as president.

